<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870224-0040 </DOCNO><HL> Slaight Unit, UPI to FormA Wire Service in Canada</HL><DD> 02/24/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CANDAPUBLISHING (PUB)TELECOMMUNICATIONS, BROADCASTING, TELEPHONE, TELEGRAPH (TEL) </IN><DATELINE> TORONTO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Standard Broadcasting Corp. said it agreed with United Press International to establish a new wire service in Canada.    Standard is a radio and television concern owned by Slaight Communications Inc., a closely held Toronto broadcaster.    The new Toronto-based service, Standard Broadcast Wire, will offer Canadian news and UPI international reports to Canadian radio and television stations. </TEXT></DOC>